        <name xml:lang="en">nitrogen, liquid</name>
        <unitName xml:lang="en">kg</unitName>
        <comment xml:lang="en">Calculated based on literature data published by the GENDORF Chemical Park. The factory produced an average of 2462760 tonnes of chemical substances (including intermediates) per year in the years 2015-2019. The average consumption of nitrogen, liquid in the years 2015-2019 was 29168033 m3 per year. This equals 0.014812 kg/kg chemical produced. The density to convert to kg was assumed to be 1.2506 kg/m3.
Since this process comprises 5 reactions to produce the final product, the default value was scaled up. To produce 1 kg of output, 2.744520043 kg of intermediate products are necessary. The value was therefore scaled up with the factor 3.74.

